# 📐 Layout & Structure Standards

## ✅ Form Layout (MANDATORY)

Follow consistent layout for all dialogs/forms:

```tsx
<div className="w-full bg-white rounded-t-xl animate-in slide-in-from-bottom-2 duration-300 shadow-lg">
  <div className="flex flex-col h-full">
    <div className="flex flex-col gap-2 p-6 flex-1">{/* Inputs */}</div>
    <div className="flex items-center justify-between gap-3 p-6">{/* Actions */}</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

* `gap-2` for inputs, `gap-3` for buttons
* `p-6` padding, `flex-1` for scroll
* FAB: Close left, Action right

## 🧩 Component Architecture

* Feature-based + atomic structure
* All components must use Shadcn
* No direct use of Radix or custom styles outside theme tokens
* Standard height for inputs/buttons: `h-12` (48px); sm: `h-10`, lg: `h-14`
* Version and document major design system changes
* Maintain backward compatibility for shared components or document breaking changes

## 📲 Responsive & Mobile-First Design

* iOS-first design, responsive to tablets/desktops
* Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
* Touch targets ≥ 44px
* Fullscreen feel on mobile (`viewport-fit=cover`)
* Scroll lock when modals/inputs open

## 🖱 Context Menus & Lists

* Use Shadcn ContextMenu
* Include consistent icon sizes (`w-4 h-4 mr-2`) and spacing (`px-3 py-3`, `gap-3`)
* List items: must support drag & drop (if needed), context menus, and edit in-place via `EditList`
